Q: Please make a python code to interpret the sepsis physiophenotypes (phenotypes derived and stratified by physiomarkers of ECG, PPG and RESP waveforms and their summary statistics- mean, percentile25, percentile75, skewness, entropy from the data of 5min just prior to sepsis-3 onset) by analyzing cluster_labels and data (shown in context). Make a interpretation report and Name the phenotypes.
A:
1. Explanation:

This code analyzes cluster labels produced by your consensus clustering and the associated physiomarker features (ECG, PPG, RESP and their summary statistics) and produces an interpretation report for each phenotype cluster. It computes per-cluster summaries (means, z-scores relative to global distribution, top distinguishing features), groups features by modality and statistic, creates short interpretable phenotype names using simple heuristics (e.g., "High ECG irregularity & elevated PPG amplitude"), saves textual and table reports and generates diagnostic plots (heatmap of normalized cluster means and boxplots of top features). It also returns a programmatic dictionary of cluster interpretations for downstream use.

2. Modified Code:

